-- Anglo American Says Four Drayton Coal Mine Staff Hospitalized After Blast
-- Ben Sharples
-- 2010-07-23T02:46:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/anglo-american-says-four-drayton-coal-mine-staff-hospitalized-after-blast.html

          
          
             Anglo American Plc said four workers
at its Drayton coal mine in Australia’s New South Wales state
were hospitalized after they were injured during blast
activities.  
 Five employees were in the immediate vicinity of the
incident and all received medical attention, Anglo American said
in an e-mailed statement. Of the four treated at hospital, one
has been discharged and the fifth employee affected by the
incident has returned to work.  
 Anglo American said it is treating the incident “very
seriously” and cooperating with all relevant authorities.  
